Dashboards and reports
  •	Dashboards and reports in Xray (for Jira) provide visual insights into testing progress, coverage, and quality using customizable gadgets on Jira dashboards
  •	Dashboard is a customizable view using gadgets to visualize testing progress, requirements coverage, and test execution status, helping teams monitor quality,
    identify blockers, and report to stakeholders.


Key Features & Benefits:
  Visual Dashboards: Create customizable dashboards in Jira with Xray gadgets to display test progress, quality, and bottlenecks.
  Test Coverage: Visualize coverage linking tests to requirements to see what's covered and what's missing.
  Execution Tracking: Monitor pass/fail rates, execution trends, and overall test status over time.
  Defect Analysis: Identify defects, see linked issues, and understand defect trends.
  Traceability: Link tests to requirements for comprehensive traceability.
  Customization: Use Xray gadgets and Jira's built-in options for tailored views. 
